==In project management==
In [[project management]], quality control requires the project manager and/or the project team to inspect the accomplished work to ensure its alignment with the project scope.&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite web|last= Phillips |first= Joseph |title= Quality Control in Project Management |url= http://www.pmhut.com/quality-control-in-project-management |date=November 2008 |publisher=The Project Management Hut |access-date=21 December 2012 }}&lt;/ref&gt; In practice, projects typically have a dedicated quality control team which focuses on this area.&lt;ref name=&quot;RoseProject14&quot;&gt;{{cite book |title=Project Quality Management: Why, What and How |author=Rose, K.H. |publisher=J. Ross Publishing |pages=224 |year=2014 |isbn=9781604271027}}&lt;/ref&gt;

