      <format>text/x-wiki</format>
      <text bytes="701" xml:space="preserve">{{short description|Half the vertex angle of the cone of light emitted at the exit face of an optical fiber}}
In [[fiber optics]], the '''radiation angle''' is half the [[vertex angle]] of the cone of [[light]] emitted at the exit face of an [[optical fiber]].  

The cone boundary is usually defined (a) by the angle at which the [[far-field]] [[irradiance]] has decreased to a specified fraction of its maximum value or (b) as the cone within which there is a specified fraction of the total radiated [[Power (physics)|power]] at any point in the [[far field]].

